    "desc": "The Players’ Tribune is a sports media company that provides athletes with a platform to connect directly with their fans, in their own words.",
    "navbar": "",
    "text": "Please note: This website includes an accessibility system. Press Control-F11 to adjust the website to the visually impaired who are using a screen reader; Press Control-F10 to open an accessibility menu.\nBASKETBALL\nFOOTBALL\nSOCCER\nHOCKEY\nBASEBALL\nMORE SPORTS\nVIDEOS\nSILENCE IS NOT AN OPTION\nKNUCKLEHEADS\nLETTER TO MY YOUNGER SELF\nMENTAL HEALTH AWARENESS\nTRUSS LEVELZ\nBLINDSIDED\nTPT ASSIST\nWhat Milan Means to Me\nFikayo Tomori\nThank You, Tennessee\nHendon Hooker\nPhotos of 2022\nThe Players' Tribune\nMark Cuban\nDarius Miles, Mark Cuban, Quentin Richardson\nMOST RECENT\nLet’s Do This, St. Louis!\nWillson Contreras will be playing for the St. Louis Cardinals: “This is truly going to be one of the great honors of my entire life.”\nWillson Contreras\nI’m Still Here\nJohn Wall shares his story: “I was this close to taking my own life. That’s a hard thing to tell the world. But if you can say one thing about me, it’s that I’ve always been real, and that’s not going to change today.”\nJohn Wall\nY’all Don’t Know a Damn Thing About JaMarcus Russell\nJaMarcus Russell shares his truth: “It’s my turn to speak on it. If you wanna judge me, then judge me. But at least know where I come from first.” \nJaMarcus Russell\nI Want to Remember Everything\nMikaela Shiffrin on losing her dad and the real nature of grief: “Some days, it’s so hard to put one foot in front of the other. That’s grief. That’s being a human.”\nMikaela Shiffrin\nFEATURED STORY\nI’m Glad I’m a Horned Frog\nDon’t sleep on Max Duggan and TCU Football: “We’ve been READY, no matter what, especially when we’ve faced adversity.”\nMax Duggan\nLetter to My Younger Self\nPelé\nFROM THE ARCHIVE\nWorking My Way to the Big Leagues\nKelsie Whitmore on playing baseball: “This has been a real journey. To get to this point. It’s not been smooth sailing, that’s for sure.” \nKelsie Whitmore\nI’m That Bitch\nThis is Jade Cargill in her own words.\nJade Cargill\nFootball Has No Gender\nGrowing up, it was Alexia Putellas’ dream to play for Barcelona. Now, she’s a Barça midfielder and a Ballon d’Or winner.\nAlexia Putellas\nWORLD CUP 2022\nThrough the Lens: USMNT Fans\nThe Players’ Tribune captured some of the madness during the U.S. team’s opening games against Wales and England.\nThe Players' Tribune\nOnly Fate Can Explain this Story\nThis is the life of Rodrygo: “Words have power. Man, I’m living proof.” \nRodrygo\nA Message to Everyone Going to Qatar\nTim Sparv has a message ahead of the World Cup in Qatar: “Staying silent when you see injustice, that’s just not cool anymore.” \nTim Sparv\nLETTER TO MY YOUNGER SELF\nLetter to My Younger Self\nBrandi Chastain pens a letter to her younger self: “People will remind you to never look back — always look forward, in positivity and hopefulness.”\nBrandi Chastain\nLetter to My Younger Self\nDerek Jeter pens a letter to his younger self: “You’re going to live out your wildest dreams. You’ll be a Yankee. A champion. Even a Hall of Famer.”\nDerek Jeter\nLetter to My Younger Self\nTarik Cohen pens a letter to his younger self: “It’s almost like, for you, nothing can just be easy and work out and make everyone happy.”\nTarik Cohen\nLetter to My Younger Self\n“It’s 1991, you’re 35-and-a-half years old, you have two bad knees and seven months left on your contract…you’re going to become a professional wrestler.”\nDiamond Dallas Page\nABOUT\nATHLETE APPLICATION\nCAREERS\nPRIVACY\nTERMS\nCOOKIE POLICY\nNEWSLETTER\nACCESSIBILITY STATEMENT\nCookies Settings\n© 2023\nMinute Media\n- All Rights Reserved",
